[[ch01-war]]
== War

The first chapter is about war because when people think about manifestos they think Utopia. In 2024 a book titled, "Abundance", came out as a manifesto for Utopia. This book is about perpetual war society.

There is a great lyric by a 70s rock band "Foreigner" that encapsulates the usage of the word war in New Democracy,

"I'm at war with the world, and that's the way it should be." - Foreigner

Survival is war with the world. If it ever comes down to destroying the Earth in order for our species to survive on Mars, then we must destroy Earth. This is context with which the word war is used within New Democracy society. Asteroid defense against asteroids destroying Earth is proper use of the word war. We are at war with asteroids that collide with Earth and we must defend ourselves. Humans, animals, and environment are all considered valid agents of war.

The word "war" today has lost all meaning. The US has sunk fishing boats near Venezuela. If Venezuela sunk fishing ships near the US then the US most definitely consider that an "act of war." This was certainly the case after a terrorist attack on 9/11. The US retaliated by declaring war on eight different countries. Well, we didn't declare war. We authorized use of military force in Iraq and then used that for the other seven countries. The word "war" today has lost all meaning.

What is war? Radio was a mainstream until the Internet took off as a mass communication platform in the mid 2000s. Radio broadcast such public forums as, "The World Affairs Council" and the "Common Wealth Club" to name two. One topic that always broke my heart as intensely as pique my interest was that of land mines.

The US planted thousands of land mines as part of the Vietnam War the ended in 1972. However, the US never removed them. As a result then people were regularly injured and killed by stepping on land mines long after the war ended. Various public charity efforts within the US gave speeches on the radio to raise awareness and money. Evidently because our US military spending couldn't appropriated for war clean up.

When a Vietnamese citizen steps on a land mine today, in 2025, and dies then how is that death classified? Natural causes? No. Murder? An act of war? Clearly the death resulted from an act of war.

War cannot be defined without first considering what is murder, intentional killing by humans. We currently don't consider death by pollution poisoning as murder. Even if the pollution was intentional and the toxicity known. The lead poisoning of lead pipes in Flint Michigan is good example. Lead was known as a poison when those pipes were installed.

Anyone who watches modern cop shows, legal shows, and so on knows about felony murder. The driver of the get-away car is liable for murder even if they didn't know a murder was a possible outcome. 

Murder has a word is vague. If someone poisons someone deliberately but that death doesn't occur until after one year then that person did not commit murder by statute of limitations even though the statute of limitations for murder has no limit. Further, indirect intentional killing such as with pollution knowingly have death risks is not considered murder. However, the use of biological agents is considered murder and an act of war and a war crime. 

Murder and war are two concepts that are nebulous in use because their use is intimately tied to justice and our legal systems. Various legal systems have widely varying definitions of these terms. It is because of this the Geneva Conventions was convened so as to create international legal definitions of war and murder.

There is no justice system in New Democracy. There is no rule of law. Humans are incentivized to not kill each other in better ways than a justice system that primarily focuses on the poor. These ways are discussed later on this book. For now we just need to know definitions like war and murder that are bond to legal use no longer apply because legal systems do not exist.

New Democracy is fundamentally based upon survival and not justice or the rule of law. Survival is divided into two components: war and quality of life.

The first two-hundred thousands years or human existence was a hunter-gatherer existence. Humans were at war with all animals including humans. Humans were prey or at least killed by animals, such as any animal that currently exists in Australia. :) Just kidding.

The point is that humans were at war with all animals as they didn't understand what was lethal and what was not. Further humans were at war with the rest of the environment. This is an evolutionary adaptation use of the word war. We had to adapt to sleeping at night in caves for defense and hunt during the day when groups of humans were most effective at group killing.

Human quality of life was limited to mostly socializing. Socializing is still the most important quality of life.


New Democracy frames reality such that we are at war with anything threatening our survival. Quality of life comes secondary to that. Life gets complicated because lack quality of life threatens our survival too so there is limit on focusing merely on survival. Give me liberty or give me death. Humans cannot live by bread alone. Understanding these limits is fundamental to New Democracy.

New Democracy is not about creating Utopia. New Democracy is about survival first and quality of life second. War is adapting to the environment. The benefit of framing adaptation as war is that defenses such as walls defend against multiple animal threats, weather threats and such. Therefore when thinking of defending against a specific threat one should always consider threats in general to optimize defenses.

Further the law of unintended consequences applies. War includes allies. Humans need other life including squirrels. A wall or a road can cut squirrels off from each other and their nuts. When we think about allies of war with New Democracy we think of allies as well as enemies. This includes climate and our relationship to it as being both hostile and necessary.


We are at war. We have always have been at war. We will always be at war. New Democracy is a design of perpetual war and not of utopia. New Democracy is a war footing, not some dream of ever increasing Utopia. War includes all hostilities and not just those of humans.

War starts with microbes, bacteria and viruses. We are at war with  plants, animals and other humans. War means asteroids and the Solar system. A New Democracy society then is centered on survival first, then quality of life. Quality of life may be compromised at any time due to any kind of war.

We will always be at war with the environment because the environment throughout most of the Universe is hostile to us. An asteroid could hit tomorrow and wipe out all of animal life on Earth. We need virus and asteroid defenses as much as we need defenses from other humans. War.


Another view of war is responsibility. Old Democracy had rights. New Democracy has responsibilities. The war we are constantly engaging requires responsibilities for everything that tries to destroy us. Why? Because we are the life that can think other life. All other life is contingent on its own survival and that of any needed symbiotic environment.

We don't talk about rights in New Democracy. We talk about responsibilities. Those responsibilities extend to everything that might destroy us. We need to manage them. The Sun will eventually destroy us as it ages. There already exist the science and physics needed to extend the life of the Sun indefinitely. We need to take on that responsibility. Every day we are at war with the Sun in the form of the weather.

Two Core Directives

New Democracy doesn't have a constitution nor does it have a legal system. New Democracy has two core directives that replace ideology.

1. Everyone in
2. Life goes on


Everyone in means we are all responsible for everyone, all humans. No exceptions. This is a mandate, an imperative. There is no competition. New Democracy is focused on survival and quality of life of everyone

Life goes on means two things.

First, life means all life like your pets. Bacteria, viruses, animals and humans are all included in life goes on. However, 99% of animal species have gone extinct so we can't have one directive of just "life goes on".. The prime directive of everyone in is prioritizes any life form that can take responsibility for all other life forms. The everyone in directive is currently limited to just humans. Life goes on includes all life forms but with the understanding the life forms go extinct and may need to be sacrificed to maintain human life, any life that manages all other life.

Second, life goes on means indefinitely in time. The easiest way to think about this is to realize our current understanding is that this Universe will die of heat death in trillions of years. We must prevent that. The Andromeda galaxy is expected to collide with the Milky Way in two billion years. We need to manage that. The Sun is expected to burn up the Earth in 7.5 billion years. The Earth is 4.5 billion years old. There already exists the physics to maintain the Sun in its current state even though we lack the engineering.


One immediate implication of life goes on is that it prioritizes existing within this Universe over all else. This means all religions and ideologies that prioritize some after life or end times is null and void in New Democracy. They are not supported.

The Weird Recipe

I'm neurodivergent. I'm not autistic but the lifestyle is the same. I have an array of exercises and processes specifically to manage mental failures. Weird is just another Tuesday as the saying goes.

Some of the mental failures I manage are common to neurotypicals who are 80-85% of individuals that show a natural, almost unconscious inclination to conform to social norms and expectations. One such common failure is fear of death.

Fear of death is a survival instinct. Can't really call it a failure in this survival context. However, fear of death most useful in real-time. That fear kicks in our fight or flight nature.

Fear of death as a social value compromises long term planning for millions, billions and trillions of years that far exceed our lifespan.

My fear of death is stems from an abusive childhood where on any given day I was afraid of being killed by my parents. My childhood was spent defending myself from that threat. My fear of death was needed and necessary and greatly incorporated into my social processes. However, once I left home at the age of seventeen the fear of death social behaviors worked against me. I was super paranoid that everyone was treating my like my parents.

I was a weird person, neurodivergent, with a childhood social character anchored in real-time survival behaviors that ran counter to long term objectives. For example, even though I had a full scholarship to Purdue University I dropped out of college my first semester. I had social anxiety of emotionally crushing proportions. I was aware I had deal with it and resigned to drop out of college and come back to it in ten years? Why ten years? Because that was my guesstimate based on reading I was doing at that time on managing mental and emotional behavior.

All this is just my happy way of saying this happy recipe of weird is how I manage fear of death that crushed my long term goals coming out of childhood.


First, fear of death is its own thing. Fear of death is not secondary circumstances or derived using reason from circumstances. Fear is primal. This means it cannot be erased. Fear of death needs to be mitigated.

How? By pigeonholing it. A pigeonhole idea is one that is used for a single purpose to stuff a mental pigeon in. In this case the pigeon is fear of the death. The pigeonhole is this recipe.

This recipe is a single-use thought experiment. When people think of thought experiments it is common to think of Schrodinger's cat. Schrodinger's cat. In the thought experiment, a hypothetical cat in a closed box may be considered to be simultaneously both alive and dead while it is unobserved, as a result of its fate being linked to a random subatomic event that may or may not occur.

The weird experiment is similar to  Schrodinger's cat in that it addresses a paradox, the weird.

The paradox: no matter how weird you can imagine life, life is far weirder. However, you fear of death management requires you to continue to increase on the amount of weird you understand.

I understand life. When I say that what I mean is that as I increase how weird I understand life to be, it is never weird enough. Sometimes we hear this concept explained as "the more you know, the more you know you don't know". This recipe explains the process for expanding your weird understanding.

Here's the recipe. This is all fiction.

Summary: our universe is created out of substance as an experiment to increase known data of the substance, i.e. to find something interesting. The experiment is set to terminate after a certain time if certain uninteresting thresholds are never exceeded. You will be resurrected by humans in billions of years in this effort to find something interesting.

Imagine a single frame cartoon. This cartoon depicts a movie theater entrance. The entrance sells tickets in order to gain entrance. A tell stands behind a class window with a cut out for exchanging cash for tickets. The employee behind the window has cash in her hand and says in a text bubble, "One ticket? Really"? The person buying the ticket is in fact a set of Russian nesting dolls.

In our though experiment the Russian nesting dolls are made of substance. Substance is what matter and energy are made from. Substance has always existed and precedes time. Substance just is. Substance eventually gains time. Substance eventually gains consciousness. Substance wants to understand what happened, why did time now exist and why is substance now conscious? So, substance sets out on a number of experiments to find out.

We are just one non-infinite, non-set of such experiments.

non-infinite, non-set: 1. Something with no classification because it can take any class type and size.

Substance is non-infinite, non-set. This is weird. I mean really word. There is no cost to being any class of any size. Our Universe rose out of substance as one such experiment.

Experiments require monitoring. That means this Universe is both the observation and thing being observed. If any outcome of this experiment is ever new then the substance can replay or read the complete observation of the complete observed universe.

But things get really interesting and really weird when one day substance creates an experiment than can then create other experiments. Substance settles on two like verses that then can create an unlimited number of like verses. We sometimes call this infinite recursion. We literally call this male and female.

Universes can mate and with other universes and create universes at no cost. This enables infinite experiments within a verse.

In concrete terms our genes represent our verse. Quantaum mechanics represents our Universe that can mate with other universes and create more universes.

First order verses then are the initial pair, the Adam and Eve, of a verse type.

Substance needs a way to know what's important, if a verse has new result potential. So each verse is created to expire if it doesn't exceed a certain threshold of known data. Our universe is going to expand to heat death unless we stop it. 

How does this manage fear of death. It manages fear of death because any verse that can replicate must necessarily replicate to create new data potential. This potential requires the verse to be able to playback or read the experiment observations the same as substance. This ability to both the observed and the observer means everyone can be re-constituted.

Further, New Democracy has a mandate of everyone in. Everyone includes the past. In other words, you will be resurrected by humans. New Democracy creates a system to resurrect people throughout all time and further a society you want to be resurrected in. Trust me, you don't want to be resurrected into our current state of affairs.

You will be resurrected because individual life is just that: distinct individual. New distinct data is the substance objective and thus our objective.

You will be resurrected. Weird, right?
